      <guid>/docs/desktop/addons/owasp-ptk/ptk-options/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;owasp-ptk-options&#34;&gt;OWASP PTK Options&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;enable-automated-scanning&#34;&gt;Enable Automated Scanning &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34; href=&#34;#enable-automated-scanning&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;fill-current o-60 hover-accent-color-light&#34; height=&#34;22px&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;22px&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34; fill=&#34;currentColor&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When checked, PTK will automatically run its configured scan rules during browser sessions. When unchecked, PTK will still be active in the browser but no automated scanning will take place.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
